
Enable below options via menuconfig or defconfig for coredump:
CONFIG_DEBUG_COREDUMP
CONFIG_DEBUG_COREDUMP_MEMORY_DUMP_MIN

More information on zephyr coredump and above options:
https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/guides/debug_tools/coredump.html

-------------------------ARM64 Coredump parsing -----------------------------------------

1. Copy Coredump log to coredump.log
Copy from <err> coredump: #CD:BEGIN# till <err> coredump: #CD:END#

2. Convert coredump.log to coredump.bin
./scripts/coredump/coredump_serial_log_parser.py coredump.log coredump.bin

3.Start zephyr gdb server
./scripts/coredump/coredump_gdbserver.py build/zephyr/zephyr.elf coredump.bin

4.Start gdb client from zephyr aarch64 toolchain
e.g. toolchain installed at  ~/opt/zephyr-sdk/
~/opt/zephyr-sdk/aarch64-zephyr-elf/bin/aarch64-zephyr-elf-gdb build/zephyr/zephyr.elf

5. Inside gdb connect to target
target remote localhost:1234
